==English==
===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/jiːt/}}
* {{audio|en|En-au-yeet.ogg|Audio (AU)}}
* {{rhymes|en|iːt|s=1}}
===Etymology 1===
Popularized by a 2014 video uploaded on {{w|Vine (service)|Vine}}.<ref>{{cite web |en |url=https://www.bustle.com/articles/103093-what-does-yeet-mean-how-do-you-use-it-heres-the-backstory-on-the-dance |work={{w|Bustle (magazine)|Bustle}} |publisher=Bustle Digital Group |author=Mehak Anwar |date=2015-08-14 |accessdate=2022-09-07 |title=Here's Why People Are Suddenly Saying "Yeet"}}</ref> Examples of an interjection which sounds like this being uttered while throwing something can be found as early as 1998 (by British presenter [[w:Jeremy Clarkson|Jeremy Clarkson]]) and 1999 (in the ''King of the Hill'' episode "To Kill a Ladybird").
